Deal Note
PROBABLY GENETIC: Direct-to-consumer rare genetic disease tests

Probably Genetic (http://www.probablygenetic.com) is a company from the current Y Combinator batch (YC W19). They help people with genetic diseases get diagnosed using DNA tests. It’s a simple at-home saliva test you will soon be able to order from their website.

Here is Lukas, the CEO, pitching at YC Demo Day: https://goo.gl/cf6mQf

When I saw this pitch at Demo Day, I immediately got up to go find them. Two of my siblings suffer from rare diseases, and I'm deeply familiar with the space and the challenges patients face today. I've been looking for a company that takes a patient-centric approach like this for quite some time and am excited to have an allocation in their seed round.

Genetic sequencing costs are continuing to plummet and healthcare payers are increasingly waking up to the potential cost-savings of reimbursing more (and earlier) genetic testing for more patients. At the same time, it remains bizarrely difficult for patients to find the answers they need unless they get very lucky with their initial choice of physician.

I believe that Lukas and Harley—two PhDs from Oxford and Cambridge—are the right founders, building the right company at the right time. They have a shot at building a very large and massively impactful business.
